name: What's In Your Closet? Resale Boutique
directions:
In the back, just after the dressing room. 
Go to the doorway in the back with the curtains, do not go through the curtains, but go left immediately and then straight.
comment: Small family run business, owner is LGBTQ+ friendly, she's the mother of a trans guy and good friends with a trans girl, so she's fine with trans people.

name: Walmart Neighborhood Market

name: Civic Hall

name: 8th Dimension Comics & Games
directions: NW corner of West Rd. Feminist- & Trans-friendly staff will greet you. Walk to store back left, through red door into game room, restroom on right.

name: First Presbyterian Church
directions: Enter through main doors at front or back of building and ask on-site reception staff where the unisex family restroom is and they will often show you. First floor near center of building.
comment: People come and go in the church frequently, so just ask with confidence and you should be okay.

name: Umami Sushi
directions: Sushi restaurant on the West side of Hwy 6 under the overpass next to UPS store.
comment:
Not a high traffic area so they won't mind if you go in just to use restroom. Friendly staff will often greet you but you can just say you're meeting someone, if you like.

When you walk in door, go right to the end of the booths, then left and straight to the back. Restrooms mostly hidden from view, single gendered stalls.

name: A Tasting Room
directions: One general neutral bathroom with a single toliet with a sturdy lock.
comment: In the middle of the building.  The employees are LGBTQ friendly.

name: St. George's Episcopal Church
directions: One in parish hall upstairs, access through frint doors or up stairs from parking lot, two in lower hallway.
comment: building open 24-7..AA and other community groups meet there.

name: Portsmouth Brewery
directions: Through shop, in Main dining room
comment: Browse through the shop.

name: Earth Eagle Brewing Company
directions: In hallway between brewpub and shop. Two separate neutral bathrooms.  One is up a couple stairs.
comment: You could likely walk in as long as shop/restaurant are open.

name: IB's Hoagies

name: Bateman Physical Sciences Center B-E/Wexler Hall

name: Cafe dmour

comment: Very nice staff just walk on ib

name: Klinic on Broadway
directions: Across from the counselling rooms, a few steps from the entrance
comment:
Only open limited hours, Mondays & Wednesdays: Noon - 7:00 pm, Tuesdays, Fridays & Saturdays: Noon - 4:00 pm. 
Counselling is done at this location, so if you come into the building the reception person will approach you, however you should be fine if you tell them you just need the toilet.

name: Winnipeg James Armstrong Richardson International Airport
directions: Inside the terminal, past security there is a family/accessible restroom between each set of gendered restrooms.

name: Klinic
directions: One single stall restroom by the front desk. One gender neutral multi-stall restroom in the basement
comment: You might be able to just walk in, but if you tell the front desk you need a restroom they will let you use it. Klinic is trans-friendly.

name: Nine Circles Community Health Centre
directions: One near the front doors, two in the hall to the clinic.
comment: Ask for a key at the front desk. The clinic serves trans people and the receptionists shouldn't mind if you come in just to use the bathrooms.

name: Good Will Social Club
directions: In the back there are multiple gender neutral, single stall washrooms.

name: David L. Boren Student Union
directions: Second floor, hallway on the right, first door to the left.

name: Holbert Hendrix Auditorium at UNLV
directions: Front of building

name: City Target
directions: The restrooms are by the cash registers. Their are two typical gendered bathrooms, but before those there is a single "family restroom," which anybody can use.
comment: The sign says "family restroom, " but anybody can use it. As a non-binary person who works there, that is what I use. I also see people who I know are cis use it all the time. No one will question you using it yourself (as in, without a child or what have you).
